post.description:
Add a new connection with encrypted fields.

This endpoint creates BOTH the secret in AWS Secrets Manager AND the metadata in RDS.

Flow:
1. Generate connection_uuid
2. Create secret in Secrets Manager (connections/{client_uuid}/{connection_uuid})
3. Store secret name in RDS secret_arn field
4. Insert metadata into RDS with connection_uuid + secret_arn

Request body should include 'credentials' dict (actual API keys/secrets).
The secret_arn field will be auto-populated with the secret name.

Example request:
{
  "connection_details": {
    "connection_name": "Stripe Production",
    "provider_type": "stripe",
    "status": "active",
    "metadata": {
      "credentials": {
        "api_key": "sk_live_xxxxx",
        "publishable_key": "pk_live_xxxxx"
      },
      "webhook_url": "https://..."
    },
    "created_by": "user@example.com"
  }
}

